&lt;p&gt;A park concession stand run by restauranteurs, they have a few vegetarian options.  The Mushroom Burger is portabello with cheese.  The Garden Dog is a Chicago Dog without the vienna beef dog.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They make frozen custard, floats, sundaes, fries, and sell alcohol.  The custard contains egg, and the cheese is dairy based.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Eat outside in the restored Park, and even drink alcohol in the specially designated area in front.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Strictly Roots is an all-vegan ital Caribbean restaurant in the heart of Harlem.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dishes are ordered individually - they range from $1 a serving for sides to $3 a serving for main dishes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Side dishes include peas and rice and fried plantains, main dishes include fake meat dishes, tofu tempura, lasagna, etc. There are also usually bean stews for $2 a serving.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The cheese they use is Toffuti brand - kosher and vegan, no casein.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They usually have at least 1 desert for $2.50.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sukhadia&#39;s Restaurant is a completely vegetarian Indian restaurant offering both dine-in and take-out. In addition to offering traditional Northern and Southern Indian food, they offer a wide selection of Jain specialties (no garlic or onions).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They offer a wide variety of curries, rice dishes, dosas, and authentic bread and have traditional dishes like aloo gobi (cauliflower &amp;amp; potatoes) and chana masala (chickpeas, onions &amp;amp; tomatoes), but also more unique dishes like vegetable patties and roasted bread with eggplant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sukhadia&#39;s offers a sit-down &amp;quot;Grand Lunch Buffet&amp;quot; for $10.95 and a take-out lunch buffet for $4.99/lb.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is a fancy-ish dining area in the back of the restaurant and a buffet and take-out section in the front, along with a dessert case.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ta&iuml;m, located in the West Village, is an all vegetarian Middle Eastern place with a large menu and very reasonable prices. Their menu includes three kinds of falafel: regular (cilantro &amp;amp; lime), red pepper, and harissa (with Tunsanian spices), Israeli salad, hummus, tabbouleh, pickled vegetables, fries with saffron aioli, and various smoothies (both vegan and non-vegan).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Eat your food inside or take it out to their outdoor patio.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Note: they take only cash.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lotsa sandwiches, soups, salads, and brunch!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lunch specials 12-4 on weekdays, and brunches on the weekend  from 10-4:30.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lots of organic teas, juices, coffee, and vegan desserts made wheat free and made on the premises.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is located between 7th Street and St. Mark&#39;s.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Una Pizza Napoletana is a small, vegetarian pizzeria in the East Village that serves 100% handmade Neapolitan pizza that is wood-fired in a brick oven. They open at 5pm but don&#39;t have a set closing time. They bake until all the dough is gone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They serve 4 kinds of pizzas, all 12&amp;quot; and all $21: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-Marinara: tomatoes, garlic, fresh basil&lt;br /&gt;
-Margherita: tomatoes, mozzarella, fresh basil&lt;br /&gt;
-Bianca: tomatoes, mozzarella, garlic, basil&lt;br /&gt;
-Filetti: Cherry tomatoes, mozzarella, garlic, fresh basil&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The menu is small and the pizzas are very simple. No slices, no appetizers, no substitutions, no desserts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The restaurant is cozy and candle lit, and they even serve tap water in a wine bottle. Although they don&#39;t serve any appetizers, desserts, or fancy drinks, they do have a decent wine list.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Every day the Uptown Juice Bar has 20+ dishes at the counter, which can be purchased a la carte or in a small, medium, or large plate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The large plate is $9 + tax, which is your choice of 4 dishes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The choices include several fake meat dishes, such as barbecue chicken drumsticks, and tofu dishes such as Caribbean jerk tofu. Additionally there are numerous side dishes such as kale, candied yams, peas and rice, etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additionally, there are a number of menu items such as pizza and fish and chips that can be ordered individually.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In front is the juice bar which offers dozens of freshly made smoothies and juices, and homemade breads and deserts.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Vegetarian Indian dinner set in a bi-level dining room, which resembles an Indian village.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The prix fixe meal for $22.95 comes with three courses: appetizer, entree, and dessert.  It is all you can eat lacto-Vegetarian/Vegan.  You simply point and ask for whichever items you want more of.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Make sure to make reservations in advance.  They are absolutely necessary for weekends and Friday nights.&lt;/p&gt;
